The Northern Cape is on a drive to improve the education system in the province. Premier Dr Zamani Saul wants the province to return to the glory days of top matric results. Efforts to change this situation include extended matric camps and the training of teachers. Over 200 science and mathematics teachers are now being trained. The Edukit teaching program will help in lesson preparation and understanding of CAPS-aligned content. Teachers were supplied with laptops and tablets loaded with the relevant subject content. Mac Jack, MEC for education in the province says the department is going to include the private sector to ensure that this initiative is financially viable. FOR MORE, WATCH VIDEOS BELOW:  